not accrete any material\nfrom objects larger than 500-1000km. The large Earth-to-Moon HSE abundance\nratio is explained if the late veneer included large impactors (D >=\n500-1000km) regardless of their size distribution, as long as most of Earth's\nveneer came from large bodies. The spin angular momenta imparted by stochastic\nlate veneer impacts was far in excess of the current ones for Mercury and\nVenus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2013 20:00:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
